## Structured Logging — structlog

```python
import structlog
logger = structlog.get_logger()

# GOOD — always bind correlation context
log = logger.bind(job_id=str(job.id), repo=repo.full_name, pr_number=job.pr_number)
await log.ainfo("review_job_started", agent="security")
await log.aerror("gemini_call_failed", error=str(e), attempt=attempt)

# BAD
print(f"job started: {job.id}")  # ❌ never use print
logger.info("something happened")  # ❌ no correlation context
```

Required fields on every log entry: `job_id`, `repo`, `pr_number`.
Never log: JWT tokens, access tokens, raw webhook payloads, or any field ending `_encrypted`.

---

## Clean Architecture — Import Rules

```python
# domain/ — no external imports
from domain.entities.review import Review           # ✅
from infrastructure.db.models import ReviewORM      # ❌ never in domain

# application/ — domain only
from domain.repositories.i_review_repository import IReviewRepository  # ✅
from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession     # ❌ never in application

# infrastructure/ — anything goes
from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession     # ✅
from domain.repositories.i_review_repository import IReviewRepository  # ✅ (implementing)

# api/ — application use cases + schemas only
from application.use_cases.get_review import GetReviewUseCase  # ✅
from infrastructure.db.repositories import PostgresReviewRepository  # ❌
```

---

## Dependency Injection — container.py

Use cases receive dependencies via constructor injection. Never instantiate dependencies inside a use case.

```python
# GOOD — injected
class GetReviewUseCase:
    def __init__(self, review_repo: IReviewRepository) -> None:
        self._repo = review_repo

# BAD — hard-coded
class GetReviewUseCase:
    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self._repo = PostgresReviewRepository()  # ❌ hard-coded infrastructure
```

All wiring is in `api/dependencies/container.py` only.

---

## Gemini Client — Structured Output Only

```python
# GOOD — Pydantic schema enforces output structure
class SecurityOutput(BaseModel):
    findings: list[FindingSchema]

result: SecurityOutput = await gemini_client.generate(prompt, schema=SecurityOutput)

# BAD — free-form text parsing is fragile
raw = await gemini_client.generate_text(prompt)
findings = json.loads(raw.text)  # ❌ breaks on any LLM deviation
```

---

## Naming Conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Files | `snake_case.py` | `review_repository.py` |
| Classes | `PascalCase` | `StartReviewUseCase` |
| Interfaces | `I` prefix | `IReviewRepository` |
| Async functions | `async def` always | `async def execute(...)` |
| Private methods | `_` prefix | `_validate_signature` |
| Enums | `PascalCase` class, `UPPER_CASE` values | `Severity.CRITICAL` |
| Constants | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS = 3` |

